data-sigil="comment-body"><a href="/christine.crowe.716?__tn__=R">Christine Crowe</a> hello Christine….I’m so sorry about your package…I really hope you get it soon. I’ve seen so many comment they’re  having the same issue like yours. I have no idea what happened to that website. Since we’ve been basically closed in Ontario, I have placed orders in the past with no issues. Sometimes they would even arrive in less than a week. But mid May they had a sale and they were doing some work on the website, because I wanted to place an order but shipping was not available for Canada, Hawaii and Alaska. After that, that website doesn’t work for us, you get errors, orders can’t be tracked or get lost. The thing is they’re aware of the issue but don’t fix it. I kept getting that error message above in the pic I posted, I managed to bypass it on my third try, but something told me even though I received an order received email something was off. I called Customer Service, in the end it ended up being a “ghost order” which I didn’t even know existed. It’s when you place an order and it disappears from the system even though you receive a confirmation email. Even Customer Service was nice but they tried 3 times to place the order… same problem…poof disappears. And then I had to wait for those pending charges to fall off my card. I realized from people’s comments it wasn’t just me, but a Canadian order issue. And since we still don’t have our website<span class="_5mfr"><span class="_6qdm" style="height: 16px; width: 16px; font-size: 16px; background-image: url(&quot;https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t9/3/16/1f641.png&quot;)">🙁</span></span><span class="_5mfr"><span class="_6qdm" style="height: 16px; width: 16px; font-size: 16px; background-image: url(&quot;https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t1c/3/16/1f937_1f3fb_200d_2640.png&quot;)">🤷🏻‍♀️</span></span>Anyways I hope they fix the issue soon that’s why I commented here maybe if enough people complain they’ll do something. Danner</a></div><div data-commentid="10160093422890676_10160093781965676" data-sigil="comment-body">Barbara Slight  I get confused when shopping in-store. I will choose something then a staff member will tell me if I choose 2 more I can get one free, etc. And I never know where to look for my favorites. They are not displayed well in my opinion. In the stores in my area, they display all the handsoaps together, all the lotions together, etc. Why not display all the products OF ONE FRAGRANCE together? That would make it so much easier. I'd then just go down the shelves and be able to choose three or four items of the same fragrance for a gift for someone. I end up spending far too much time searching and I get too frustrated when I shop in-store, plus they put some displays right in the center where we need to walk. We can see them just as well if they put them on the shelves. I'll take online shopping any day.</div></div><a class="_14v8" href="/ufi/reaction/profile/browser/?ft_ent_identifier=10160093422890676_10160093781965676&amp;av=100051191839489&amp;__tn__=R"
